                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.857 L 97/126½a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <persName
                            type="to">Colonel E. M. House</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-11T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1916—6 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. 2. <hi rend="italic">Lusitania</hi> case progressing. Satisfactory settlement
                    probable. Germany apparently believes if case settled it will leave only matters
                    with Great Britain unsettled and some action will be necessary.</p>
                <closer>[File copy not signed]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
